  "prompt": "Why did Myntra acquire Jabong?",
  "response": "Myntra acquired Jabong in 2016 to strengthen its position in the Indian e-commerce fashion market. At that time, Jabong was a significant online fashion retailer, and the acquisition helped Myntra:\n\n1. Expand its market share: By acquiring Jabong, Myntra increased its customer base and market presence in the online fashion retail segment.\n\n2. Reduce competition: The acquisition eliminated a key competitor in the market.\n\n3. Leverage complementary strengths: Jabong had a different customer segment and brand portfolio that could complement Myntra's existing offerings.\n\n4. Achieve economies of scale: The merger allowed for cost savings and operational efficiencies.\n\nThe acquisition was part of Myntra's strategy to consolidate its position in the Indian e-commerce fashion market, which was increasingly competitive with players like Amazon and Flipkart. Jabong was acquired by Myntra's parent company Flipkart for approximately $70 million, further solidifying its position in the online retail space.",
